# =============================================================================
# SCRIPTED EVENT: The Dominican Republic, April 1965
# =============================================================================

@lbj_ev_dominican
title: Santo Domingo
is-card: true
card-image: img/foreign.png
on-arrival: lbj_ev_dominican = 1
view-if: lbj_year = 1965 and lbj_month = 4 and lbj_ev_dominican = 0
new-page: true

There is a coup in the Dominican Republic.

The previous government has been overthrown. There is fighting in the streets of Santo Domingo. There are, your advisors tell you, American citizens at risk. There is also, your advisors tell you, credible intelligence of communist involvement in the rebel faction.

You have to decide in the next twelve hours whether to send in the Marines.

The precedent is what worries you. You send in the Marines to a Latin American country and the headline writes itself: *LBJ Invades Caribbean Nation.* The legacy of gunboat diplomacy, which everyone in this hemisphere has not forgotten, is on the other side of this decision.

But there are Americans at risk. And the intelligence about communist involvement is credible.

- @lbj_dominican_intervene: Send in the Marines. Protect American lives.
- @lbj_dominican_wait: Wait for more information. Don't move yet.
- @lbj_dominican_oas: Work through the OAS. Multilateral response.

@lbj_dominican_intervene
title: The Johnson Doctrine
on-arrival: lbj_military -= 5; lbj_antiwar += 8; lbj_liberals -= 7; lbj_credibility -= 5; lbj_approval -= 3; lbj_continuity -= 3; lbj_far_right -= 4

Twenty-two thousand Marines and paratroopers. The largest American military intervention in Latin America since the 1920s.

The Americans are evacuated. The communist threat, if it existed at the scale the intelligence suggested, does not materialize. Order is restored.

The Latin American ambassadors are very polite when they come to register their concerns. Their governments issue statements. The phrase *"Yankee imperialism"* appears in the international press more than you would like.

The anti-war movement has found a second argument.

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

@lbj_dominican_wait
title: More Information
on-arrival: lbj_credibility += 3; lbj_liberals += 3; lbj_antiwar -= 3; lbj_continuity -= 2; lbj_approval += 1

You ask for another twelve hours.

In twelve hours the situation clarifies enough that a proportional response is possible. A smaller force. A more defensible rationale. The Americans are evacuated. The situation stabilizes.

The conservatives call it weakness. The liberals call it prudence. The Latin American ambassadors are more comfortable with the outcome.

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

@lbj_dominican_oas
title: Multilateral
on-arrival: lbj_credibility += 4; lbj_liberals += 5; lbj_antiwar -= 4; lbj_capital -= 8; lbj_approval += 2

You work through the Organization of American States. Slower. More complicated. Genuinely multilateral.

The OAS sends an inter-American force. The Americans are evacuated. Order is restored through a process that has regional legitimacy.

The Latin American press is significantly more favorable. This will matter in ways that are hard to see right now and will be more visible later.

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

# =============================================================================
# SCRIPTED EVENT: The Six-Day War, June 1967
# =============================================================================

@lbj_ev_sixday
title: The Hotline
is-card: true
card-image: img/foreign.png
on-arrival: lbj_ev_sixday = 1; lbj_military += 4; lbj_continuity += 2
view-if: lbj_year = 1967 and lbj_month = 6 and lbj_ev_sixday = 0
new-page: true

Israel has launched preemptive strikes against Egypt, Jordan, and Syria.

You found out from the news, which is not how you prefer to find out about events of this magnitude. The intelligence community is scrambling. The State Department is scrambling. The hotline to Moscow is active.

Six days from now, Israel will control the Sinai, the West Bank, the Golan Heights, and the Gaza Strip. The map of the Middle East will be permanently changed. None of this is yet known. What is known is that the war has started and the Soviets are watching and you have approximately three hours to decide what the American posture is.

- @lbj_sixday_support: Support Israel. Make the American position clear.
- @lbj_sixday_neutral: Call for a ceasefire from all parties. Stay neutral.
- @lbj_sixday_hotline: Focus on the Soviets. Use the hotline to prevent escalation.

@lbj_sixday_support
title: American Position
on-arrival: lbj_military -= 3; lbj_credibility += 2; lbj_approval += 2; lbj_antiwar += 4; lbj_continuity += 2

You make the American position clear. You are not neutral. Israel is an ally.

The Soviets receive this message through official channels. The war ends in six days. The Soviets do not intervene. The ceasefire holds.

You have a substantially more complicated Middle East to manage for the rest of your presidency. The conditions of the new map will define American foreign policy for decades.

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

@lbj_sixday_neutral
title: All Parties
on-arrival: lbj_credibility -= 2; lbj_liberals += 3; lbj_antiwar -= 2; lbj_approval -= 1

You call for an immediate ceasefire from all parties. The Israelis do not observe it. The Arabs do not observe it. The war ends in six days.

Your neutrality has made everyone slightly unhappy with you, which is sometimes what genuine neutrality looks like.

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

@lbj_sixday_hotline
title: The Hotline
on-arrival: lbj_credibility += 4; lbj_military -= 2; lbj_continuity -= 2; lbj_approval += 1

You are on the hotline to Kosygin within the hour.

The conversation is careful. Both of you are trying to communicate that neither of you wants this to become a superpower confrontation. Both of you succeed in communicating this.

The war ends in six days. The Soviets do not intervene. The hotline, used for the first time in a genuine crisis, works as designed.

This is, you think, what diplomatic infrastructure is for.

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

# =============================================================================
# SCRIPTED EVENT: Czechoslovakia, August 1968
# Warsaw Pact invasion. LBJ's options are extremely limited.
# =============================================================================

@lbj_ev_czechoslovakia
title: Prague
is-card: true
card-image: img/foreign.png
on-arrival: lbj_ev_czechoslovakia = 1; lbj_unity -= 4; lbj_credibility -= 5; lbj_approval -= 3; lbj_military += 6; lbj_continuity += 3
view-if: lbj_year = 1968 and lbj_month = 8 and lbj_ev_czechoslovakia = 0
new-page: true

Soviet and Warsaw Pact tanks have entered Czechoslovakia.

The Prague Spring — the liberalization experiment that Alexander Dubček has been running since January, the one your administration has been watching with cautious optimism — is over. The Soviets have decided they cannot tolerate a socialist state with a human face on their western border, and they have acted with the directness that is Brezhnev's particular quality.

There is nothing you can do militarily. You are fighting a war in Southeast Asia. You have no appetite for a confrontation with the Soviet Union in Central Europe in an election year. NATO is watching. The Europeans are watching. The Czechs are watching from under Soviet tanks.

What you can do is respond. The question is how loudly.

- @lbj_czech_strong: Condemn it forcefully. Cancel planned summits.
- @lbj_czech_moderate: Condemn it. Keep diplomatic channels open.
- @lbj_czech_quiet: Respond quietly. Don't jeopardize arms control talks.

@lbj_czech_strong
title: Full Condemnation
on-arrival: lbj_credibility += 4; lbj_military -= 5; lbj_approval += 2; lbj_continuity += 2; lbj_unity -= 3

You cancel the planned summit with Kosygin. You give a strong public statement. You call the invasion a violation of international law and the UN Charter.

The Soviets listen and continue the invasion. The tanks stay in Prague.

You have said the right thing. The right thing has accomplished nothing material. This is the condition of great power politics when you are fighting a war elsewhere and cannot threaten a war here.

The far right says you are weak. You say the alternative is nuclear war. Nobody is satisfied.

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

@lbj_czech_moderate
title: Calibrated Response
on-arrival: lbj_credibility += 2; lbj_approval += 1; lbj_continuity += 1; lbj_unity -= 2

You condemn the invasion clearly. You do not cancel the summit. You keep the diplomatic infrastructure intact.

The tanks stay in Prague.

You are navigating between allies who want you to do more and strategic interests that require you to do less. The navigation is imperfect. The tanks stay in Prague.

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

@lbj_czech_quiet
title: Strategic Patience
on-arrival: lbj_credibility -= 4; lbj_liberals -= 4; lbj_approval -= 3; lbj_unity -= 4; lbj_continuity -= 2

You make the calculation that arms control is more important than the statement. You respond quietly, through diplomatic channels, and keep the summit on the calendar.

The Soviets appreciate the pragmatism. The tanks stay in Prague. The arms control talks continue.

History will record both things: the pragmatism and the silence. You are not sure which it will judge more harshly.

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

# =============================================================================
# CARD: General Cold War Pressure
# The ambient weight of nuclear superpower status.
# =============================================================================

@lbj_foreign_coldwar
title: The Brief
is-card: true
card-image: img/foreign.png
tags: lbj_country_card
max-visits: 6
on-arrival: lbj_paranoia += 1

The morning intelligence brief.

Today: Soviet submarine activity in the North Atlantic is up six percent from last month's baseline. The East Germans have made three additional modifications to the Berlin wall infrastructure. A North Korean patrol boat has crossed the DMZ. A Chinese nuclear test is expected within the next thirty days.

None of this is a crisis. All of it is the permanent condition of being the leader of the free world, which is a phrase you use in public and find slightly uncomfortable in private because of what the word *free* is required to contain.

You initial the brief and move on to the budget meeting.

*(Background pressure. Nothing to decide.)*

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

